lore.item.pswg.kreetlejuice: People ignore the strange and unusual.
lore.species.pswg.aqualish.description: The swamp planet Ando hosts the humanoid Aqualish species, equipped with 4 eyes and large facial tusks.
lore.species.pswg.bith.description: Humanoid aliens native to a planet of the same name, they have large bulbous heads, massive black eyes, natural intellect, and musical talent.
lore.species.pswg.chagrian.description: Amphibious humanoids native to the ocean world Champala, Chagrians are an intimidating sight because of their tall, horn-like tentacles and blue skin.
lore.species.pswg.chiss.description: Native to Csilla in the Unknown Regions, Chiss are a near-human species with striking red eyes and blue skin.
lore.species.pswg.human.description: One of the galaxy’s most prolific species, humans are extremely adaptable to demanding conditions.
lore.species.pswg.jawa.description: A diminutive, but sentient, furry species native to Tatooine, Jawas rarely are seen without their robes.
lore.species.pswg.pantoran.description: Near-humans from the moon Pantora, Pantorans have light-blue skin, with some individuals bearing golden ancestral tattoos on their faces.
lore.species.pswg.togruta.description: Native to the grasslands of Shili, Togrutas are a humanoid species characterized by their colorful skin colors, striped head tails and face paint.
lore.species.pswg.twilek.description: Hailing from the harsh climates of Ryloth, Twi'leks are a common sight across the galaxy, easily recognized by their bright skin colors and lekku headtails.
lore.species.pswg.wookiee.description: Tall, furry humanoids from the jungle planet Kashyyyk, Wookiees are famed for their physical strength and iconic shaggy fur.
